<TEXT>
federal border patrol agents arrested two 
colombian nationals and seized about 1680 pounds of cocaine from a 
rental truck during a routine check at a turnpike gate thursday 
officials said 
the seizure not a record nationally but by far the largest in 
state history was valued at 53 million said mario ortiz 
spokesman for the immigration and naturalization service in dallas 
two men ages 25 and 27 were in custody ortiz said 
john coonce head of the drug enforcement administration office 
in tulsa said the names of the arrested men would not be released 
before friday so their identities could be confirmed 
ortiz said the cocaine was in 14 boxes in the truck which was 
otherwise loaded with new furniture 
the catch was a victory for the miami border patrol office 
which the ins had sought to close by mid1988 in a budgetcutting 
move at the insistence of the states congressional delegation 
the office was kept open with rotating agents from bordering 
states mostly to look for illegal aliens 
agents thursday would not provide details of the cocaines 
suspected origin or destination 
authorities reported confiscating 18744 pounds of cocaine along 
the usmexican border in fiscal 1987 and 3589 pounds in one 
record overland customs seizure on sept 14 1987 
the largest previous cocaine seizure in oklahoma was in 
september 1985 when agents staked out a cessna 421 in oklahoma 
city and seized nearly 725 pounds of cocaine 
</TEXT>
