<TEXT>
the federal communications commission is a 
step closer to allowing telephone companies to provide cable 
television services 
in a series of actions wednesday the fcc indicated it favors 
lifting an agency regulation and a separate law that bar telephone 
companies from running cable companies in their own service areas 
the fcc voted tentatively to recommend to congress that it 
repeal the 1984 prohibition and directed its staff to begin the 
process of repealing its own rule against such activity 
the commission called the prohibitions a draconian form of 
regulation no longer needed because the cable industry has become 
large and strong enough to compete with the telephone companies 
the fcc said allowing telephone companies to operate cable 
systems will increase services for customers including home 
shopping and video phones as well as providing an additional 
source of pay television programming 
</TEXT>
