a local priest the rev lefteris kamiris said that nov 8 the 
presidential election date is especially auspicious for the 
island 
now that michalis has the nomination theres no way hes not 
going to get elected on that day kamiris said 
kamiris said nov 8 is the feastday of st michael the patron 
saint of pelopi that day too marks the date in 1921 that 
mytilene was granted independence from turkish rule 
kamiris who paints icons sacred pictures of saints displayed 
in greek orthodox churches also was responsible for the signs 
that identify pelopi in greek and english as the hometown of 
michael dukakis 
we feel proud that someone from our island can get so far 
its changed our lives he said 
a trickle of tourists has started coming to pelopi looking for 
the dukakis family home 
all the visitors bothered us a bit at first but we dont mind 
now its good to have people wanting to visit the house where it 
all started said yiannis manolis whose father bought and 
rebuilt the ruined dukakis home in 1933 
the yellowing sale contract signed by panos dukakis the 
governors father is proudly shown to visitors 
panos dukakis emigrated to the united states in 1913 and became 
the first greekamerican to graduate from harvard medical school 
the village council already has renamed the main street michael 
dukakis street and intends to offer the presidential candidate a 
mountainside plot of land where he can build a summer home 
michalis could do some gardening maybe grow watermelons 
said stefanou who recalled that on his one and only visit to 
pelopi in 1976 the governor enjoyed the local melons 
were proud that someone who hails from pelopi might become 
the most powerful man in the world said alexander chiotellis 
who acted as dukakis host on that visit and claims to be his 
second cousin 
the villagers mostly sheep and goat breeders also say a 
dukakis election victory might improve the quality of life in 
pelopi 
if hes elected the government may finally decide to pave the 
top part of the road to the village after all if he comes here as 
president he cant drive up a dirt track stefanou said 
a selfstyled local poet already has composed what he calls an 
ode to dukakis 
dukakis comes from our village our beautiful island of 
lesbos eleftherios yiannakos recited on wednesday night 
lesbos is the ancient greek name for mytilene 
all the villagers are lovingly concerned to see him as 
president in america the 20line poem continues 
