she expects about 30000 people delegates reporters and guests 
to attend each day of the fourday event she said officials are 
looking for a way to parcel out the empty seats and still maintain 
security 
adding to the confusion and overcrowding at the democratic 
convention were an estimated 1700 people who received passes to 
get into the omni arena because of their status as bigticket 
contributors to the party 
members of the partys national finance council whose members 
give at least 5000 each its business council who give 10000 
or more apiece and its victory fund who commit to give or raise 
100000 all receive passes to the convention hall sweitzer said 
he estimated that during convention sessions about 1000 of 
those with contributor passes were actually in the hall which 
seats 12500 to 13000 people in its configuration for the 
quadrennial event thousands of seats were sacrificed to build a 
huge podium full of technical gear and press seating and skyboxes 
for television crews 
but sweitzer said contributors do not compete for the 4212 
delegate seats their passes do not permit them on the convention 
floor but give access only to guest seating high in the arena he 
said they share that space with 1170 alternates and other guests 
he said 
