here is a transcript of the speech by sen thomas 
daschle of south dakota seconding the nomination of sen lloyd 
bentsen of texas for vice president at the democratic national 
convention on thursday night 
my name is tom daschle and im here to tell you that the last 
thing we need on the prairie is another dried up old bush 
we need a change we need michael dukakis 
and we need lloyd bentsen 
south dakotans pay no greater respect to anyone than to those 
pioneers who found partnership with the land our glory comes from 
those who carved dreams from that land under a sky so vast that 
only greatness could unfold 
the bentsen family is a story of the american dream of taking 
chances of beating the odds a story of a familys life in south 
dakota and the rigors of survival in the american west a rugged 
beginning from which our roots take hold roots of american life 
that sprout qualities from which our nation draws its greatness 
roots of american soul that lend strength to our nations values 
roots from which descendants of greek and danish immigrants will 
soon become the president and vice president of the greatest 
country in the world 
and it is from these roots that values are born 
roots are not forcefed they are passed on 
values are not worn on the sleeve but come from the soul and 
emanate through the words and deeds of those who live them 
lloyd bentsens values born in the west nurtured in the south 
are now evident across this land 
like those of michael dukakis they are values of genuine 
american leadership 
a deep respect of human dignity 
a rare courage to stand up for ones beliefs 
and a profound belief that he owes the nation much more than 
this nation owes him 
as this man lives out these beliefs this nation has been paid 
back in multitude and we are the beneficiaries 
so now as he faces the american people let us confirm what we 
know that bentsen leadership is american leadership of the most 
valuable kind leadership marked not by what one says but by what 
one does 
and for those of us who call rural america home we also call 
lloyd bentsen friend someone who fights with us not against 
us for the family farm and someone who believes as we believe 
that reagan and bush are to agriculture what the drought is to 
wheat and corn someone who fights with us not against us because 
americans can win in any marketplace if the competition is fair 
and who believes as we believe that someone deathly sick in the 
countryside ought to have the same chance opportunity as someone in 
country club square 
to rural americans tonight who listen from their family farms 
who may be watching from the town cafe who may occupy a bed in a 
rural hospital or a desk in a small classroom or a counter in the 
town hardware store let me say to each one of you and to all 
americans this man stands with us on accomplishments not 
promises on values not vagaries with roots that are our roots he 
is the son of our heritage he is our friend 
so it is with humility and great pride tonight that i second the 
nomination of the next vice president of the united states sen 
lloyd bentsen 
</TEXT>
