police seized bolivias cocaine kingpin 
roberto suarez gomez after trekking through jungles all night to 
catch him by surprise asleep at his ranch the minister of the 
interior reported thursday 
in miami chief assistant us attorney richard gregorie said 
on hearing the news hes the biggest cocaine producer in the 
world he has enormous acreage in coca plants 
suarez gomez was flown to la paz from trinidad city where he 
was taken after 10 antidrug police captured him wednesday morning 
at his el sujo ranch 25 miles away interior minister juan carlos 
duran said 
el sujo is one of suarez gomezs five ranches in the heart of 
the tropical northeastern beni region 
duran said suarez gomez was asleep when 10 antidrug police took 
over the ranch confiscating 20 automatic weapons and arresting two 
bodyguards 
suarez gomez 56 is wanted in miami on drug trafficking charges 
and has been called by authorities the godfather of bolivias 
illegal cocaine trade and a major supplier of drugs to the 
medellin colombia drug cartel 
however duran told a news conference that bolivia will not 
extradite suarez gomez to the united states since he already has 
been sentenced to 15 years in prison here 
he said suarez gomez had heart problems and would be examined 
medically before being presented to the press 
the 15year sentence was handed down by a judge earlier this 
year the former rancherturneddrug baron never showed up for his 
trial and was tried convicted and sentenced in his absence on drug 
trafficking charges 
bolivia a nation of 67 million people in the center of south 
america produces a third of the cocaine that reaches us and 
european markets 
until now suarez gomez has used his money and influence to buy 
his freedom in bolivia he publicly spoke of paying off political 
figures and policemen 
duran told reporters president victor paz estenssoro says he 
is very pleased with suarez gomezs arrest and that the fight 
against drugs is the top priority of the government 
in 1980 the bolivan human rights association says suarez gomez 
helped finance the military coup that overthrew the civilian 
government of lidia gueiler tejada the interim president and 
installed a government that hired italian german and argentine 
mercenaries to undertake a campaign of terror 
under that rightwing government headed by gen luis garcia 
meza drug traffickers operated with impunity and leftwing 
political figures and labor leaders were killed tortured or 
exiled the mercenaries went after opposition figures and provided 
protection to traffickers suarez gomez was considered the main 
player on behalf of cocaine traffickers 
according to the us drug enforcement administration during 
and after the 1980 military coup suarez gomez became a close 
associate of interior minister luis arce gomez who offered him 
protection from prosecution in return for large sums of money 
i think that suarez gomezs arrest shows that bolivian police 
are serious about going after major cocaine traffickers frank 
