today on the chicago board of trade following forecasts for a 
return to hot dry weather in the midwest 
the storm system that brought badly needed rain to the 
droughtstricken region over the past several days has moved east 
the weather was expected to remain mild and dry into the weekend 
and the national weather services latest 6to10day forecast 
predicts a return to warmer and drierthannormal conditions by 
the middle of next week 
corn and wheat futures posted solid gains in early trading oats 
and soybeans were mixed but mostly higher after a sharp threeday 
decline triggered by the rain 
theyre kind of raising their heads a little bit off the floor 
