million or 78 cents a share in the second quarter of 1987 
secondquarter revenue including sales at companyoperated 
restaurants and fees from franchises rose 14 percent to 143 
billion from 124 billion more than 75 percent of the mcdonalds 
restaurants in the united states are franchised 
forty percent of the more than 500 new restaurants to be added 
each year will be located outside the united states chairman fred 
l turner said in a press statement 
maximizing sales at existing restaurants is accomplished 
through attention to operations reinvestment product development 
and refinement and effective marketing programs turner said he 
noted that the companys foreign operations are achieving economies 
of scale bringing an improvement in profitability 
the company is continuing to monitor the effects of the drought 
in the farm belt on its food commodity costs said president and 
chief executive officer michael r quinlan 
he noted that mcdonalds food costs as a percent of its sales 
have declined in both the first and second quarters of this year 
compared with 1987 in addition more than 30 percent of the 
companyoperated restaurants are located outside of the united 
states and are not necessarily affected by the drought 
in the first half of the year mcdonalds earnings rose 19 
percent to 303 million or 161 a share from 2557 million 
or 134 a share in the first six months of 1987 
firsthalf revenue was up 15 percent to 265 billion from 
231 billion a year earlier 
