hispania lineas aereas has purchased four 
advancedtechnology 737500 aircraft valued at more than 105 
million from boeing commercial airplanes boeing announced 
wednesday 
the airline based in palma de mallorca spain will take 
delivery of the 130passenger airplanes between june and august 
1991 
hispania created in august 1982 as a cooperative and 
incorporated in october 1987 now operates five new 737300 
airliners and two 737200s under leases boeing said 
hispania is the first private spanish airline to purchase planes 
directly from a manufacturer according to boeing 
the new plane features more fuelefficient and quieter engines 
aerodynamic wing improvements more onboard stowage area and wider 
aisles the company said 
the hispania order brings the total order of 737500s to 127 
made by 12 customers 
